This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with action detection in videos. The paper also mentions human-robot interaction, which suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a real-time and online algorithm, which suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions solving the detection-window association and action labelling problems, which suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with constructing action tubes, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
